  "prompt": "What universities for MS in CS should be considered with GRE - 317/340, CGPA - 9.15/10 and TOEFL - 102?",
  "response": "With a GRE score of 317, a CGPA of 9.15/10, and a TOEFL score of 102, you have a competitive profile for many reputable universities offering a Master\u2019s in Computer Science (MS in CS). Here are some options you might consider:\n\n1. **Reach Schools** (Highly competitive):\n   - Stanford University\n   - Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT)\n   - University of California, Berkeley\n   - Carnegie Mellon University\n   - California Institute of Technology (Caltech)\n\n2. **Match Schools** (Good chance of admission):\n   - University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign\n   - Georgia Institute of Technology\n   - University of Michigan, Ann Arbor\n   - University of California, San Diego\n   - University of Southern California\n\n3. **Safety Schools** (Higher chance of admission):\n   - University of California, Irvine\n   - University of Florida\n   - University of Minnesota, Twin Cities\n   - Arizona State University\n   - North Carolina State University\n\nThese recommendations are generalized, and admissions are based on more than just scores, such as personal statements, letters of recommendation, research experience, and extracurricular activities. Make sure to research each program's strengths, faculty interests, and specific admission requirements to tailor your application effectively.",
